Description:
SNURK, Sleep & Dream Big!

Did you know that the Dutch word "snurk" means "snore" in English? SNURK is a Dutch design brand, which produces high-quality "horizontal living" items.

SNURK kids duvet covers are unique and so is the production of each design! All "real life" designs are made by hand, photographed and turned into a digital print. Afterwards the production goes to Portugal and they screen print everything on the softest organic cotton. Kids love the SNURK designs such as the astronaut, ballerina, firefighter or princess and find it very special that they are all printed in "real" size. In fact it's not only a princess or astronaut kids duvet cover, but laying in there really makes you feel like one!

Did you know SNURK used a real NASA suit to produce the astronaut print and can you imagine that the soccer player had to jump more than 280 times to produce the soccer player design?

Choose the correct SNURK duvet cover size!

Please be careful choosing the correct size for your kids bedding. As you might know, every country has another standard duvet and pillow size. So check the size of the duvet, but also the size of the included pillow, to make sure it fits your bedding at home. Furthermore, please feel free to contact us if you are looking for bigger duvet covers as for example a double bed (200 x 200 cm) or super king bed (260 x 220 cm). We will try our best to make everything work.

Specifications

  • Duvet cover set with screen print
  • Made of 100% high-quality organic cotton
  • Wash inside out at 40 degrees Celsius
  • Designed in Holland, made in Portugal

Furthermore, please feel free to contact us if you are looking for bigger duvet covers as for example a double bed (200 x 200 cm) or super king bed (260 x 220 cm). We will try our best to make everything work.

  • Duvet cover set with screen print
  • Made of 100% high-quality organic cotton
  • Wash inside out at 40 degrees Celsius
  • Designed in Holland, made in Portugal

Rafa Kids - B Table with B Bench (with or without backrest)
Description:
Rafa-kids B Table: Designed by architects

Rafa-kids is based in the Netherlands, but they're also active on the international markets. The brains behind Rafa are two architects, and that's clearly visible! Agata and Arek Seredyn followed a ‘route’ that sounds familiar to us: they were browsing around for furniture for their own kids, but couldn't find what they wanted. So now they're making robust, functional and practical tables, dressers, wardrobes, etc. which they love themselves. Maybe it's because it's created by two architects, but a wardrobe made by Rafa looks rather like a showcase than a wardrobe!

Made of sterner stuff

The designs are durable, solid and a feast for the eye. What do you think of the B Table? It's such a remarkable product with all those layers of wood on top of each other in the corners, all carefully finished. Nevertheless, it's most of all been designed to be practical and functional. For example, their B Table was made to enjoy for many, many years. It has the perfect size for children of 3 years old, and goes along till they're about 8 or 9 years old. The desk is ideal to play, draw and make your homework at. And if you have two young chidren or if a friend comes over to play, then the B Table is large enough for the both of them.

Aesthetic and technical

Furniture of Rafa-kids is made in Poland of the best materials and fulfills all EU safety regulations. One of their favourites is Finnish birchwood and plywood. Everything they design is based on three principles: playfulness, creativity and beauty. Agata takes care of the aesthetic side, and Arek looks after the technical, innovative side. Their furniture pieces seem to float around and look inviting to play with. At the same time, their furniture is extremely strong and well finished. As far as we're concerned, they make a magnificent couple!

Characteristics

  • Materials: Birch plywood from Finland
  • Finish: Water-based lacquer
  • Measurements table: L110 x W50 x H60 cm
  • Length table with drawers extended: 145 cm
  • Measurements bench: L90 x W33 x H36/49 cm
  • Height bench without backrest: 36 cm
  • Height bench with backrest: 49 cm

Easy assembly

Can be very easily assembled and is therefore delivered as a do-it-yourself kit. Screws aren't necessary and the table is accompanied with a comprehensible construction manual.

Name: Dear April - Kinderdekbedovertrek + kussensloop - 100x140 cm - Sail Stripes
Short description: Brengt de lente in huis met het beddengoed van Dear April!
Description:
Combineer Dear April beddengoed met de Oliver Furniture bedden!

Dear April is een Deens merk en het zusje van Oliver Furniture. Het merk haalt haar inspiratie uit de prachtige natuurlijke omgeving tussen de zee en het bos. Met tijdloze ontwerpen en een vleugje vernieuwing, lichtheid en frisheid, weerspiegelt Dear April perfect de charme van de lente. Voor het beddengoed gebruiken ze handgemaakte patronen en kiezen zij voor duurzame materialen die ethisch verantwoord zijn en afkomstig zijn van GOTS-gecertificeerde leveranciers.

Message in a Bottle

Het symbool van de boodschap in een fles, dat dierbaar is voor Dear April, staat voor rust en het nemen van de tijd. Het merk viert de vitale energie van de lente en het positieve gevoel dat dit seizoen in ons leven brengt. Het symboliseert een brief aan een dierbare vriend of een wens die wordt losgelaten in de wind, gedragen op de zachte plukjes van een paardenbloem. Laat je verleiden door de mooie designs uit de beddengoed collectie van Dear April, en brengt dat stukje lente in huis!

Details

  • Kussensloop: 40x45 cm

Matty™ Mini Changing Mat: Hygienic and 100% water resistant

Introducing the new Leander Matty™ Mini: the perfect, safe solution for those small but significant moments. Building on the success of our original Leander Matty™ changing mat, the Matty Mini upholds the same innovative standards, bringing fresh convenience to changing stations everywhere. Crafted in Denmark from the same certified PUR foam as the original, the Matty™ Mini is free of plasticizers and harmful substances, ensuring complete peace of mind. Lightweight and portable, it makes nursing on the go both easy and secure. Durability is a hallmark of the Matty™ Mini. Designed without seams or grooves where dirt and bacteria can accumulate, it remains hygienic through years of daily use. Its water-repellent surface is not only easy to clean but can also be disinfected with a damp cloth and mild soap. Tested and certified to meet European safety and material standards, the Matty™ Mini changing mat ensures both safety and lasting quality.

A happy place

The Matty changing mat can be used for so much more than just changing diapers. For instance, use it as a place to cuddle or talk with your baby. Take a moment and give your baby a massage, make eye-contact or chitchat with them. Matty is easy to take with you and make it a happy and cozy corner wherever you are for the both of you. Also notice that the edges are slightly upright, creating an extra safety barrier. Matty is there for you, night and day.
